WEBVTT

00:01.062 --> 00:02.135
[MUTTERING]

00:02.305 --> 00:04.301
Hey, Salem,
when did you start painting?

00:04.469 --> 00:06.465
When no one would read
my screenplay.

00:06.634 --> 00:07.911
I need a creative outlet.

00:08.077 --> 00:11.281
Well, my background in this area
is pretty much limited to spin art,

00:11.443 --> 00:12.562
but I like what I see.

00:12.726 --> 00:15.930
Well, let's not forget my model.
She deserves some of the credit.

00:16.453 --> 00:19.578
Do you mind if I put my nose back?
I've gotta sneeze.

00:21.000 --> 00:27.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:38.217 --> 00:41.057
For your safety, please watch
the following video.

00:45.191 --> 00:49.318
Oh, you can read a magazine, but you
didn't have time to read my screenplay.

00:49.480 --> 00:52.878
I got through volumes one and two,
but then it seemed to drift.

00:53.047 --> 00:55.282
This is <i>Enchanted By,</i>
the magazine for witches.

00:55.452 --> 00:57.573
Anything in there
about dating mortals?

00:57.736 --> 00:59.811
You'll do anything to work the fact
that you're dating

00:59.981 --> 01:01.498
into the conversation.

01:01.664 --> 01:02.736
That's not true.

01:02.907 --> 01:04.104
Has anyone seen my book bag?

01:04.269 --> 01:05.786
The guy I'm dating has books.

01:06.754 --> 01:09.228
Sabrina, I want you to check out
this month's <i>Enchanted By.</i>

01:09.400 --> 01:11.795
There happen to be some
very edifying articles.

01:11.965 --> 01:13.322
"Nose Warts: How to Hide Them."

01:13.488 --> 01:15.210
Oh, good, it's got pictures.

01:15.372 --> 01:17.048
The guy I'm dating has a nose.

01:18.177 --> 01:19.580
Okay, I'll stop.

01:19.741 --> 01:22.466
I want you to read the bulletin
from the Witches' Council.

01:22.626 --> 01:24.667
They're advising witches
under the age of 21

01:24.831 --> 01:26.632
to refrain from charitable magic.

01:26.795 --> 01:28.995
Whew, relieved of the burden
of helping others.

01:29.159 --> 01:32.523
Charitable magic can have disastrous
long-term consequences.

01:32.687 --> 01:34.409
For instance,
the teenage witch in Ohio

01:34.570 --> 01:36.645
who zapped away
her best friend's acne.

01:36.815 --> 01:38.731
- How thoughtful.
- Seemed that way,

01:38.899 --> 01:39.891
but as it turns out,

01:40.061 --> 01:43.745
her best friend was destined
to one day discover a cure for acne.

01:43.909 --> 01:45.312
So now, no cure.

01:45.472 --> 01:47.628
And now,
instead of being a scientist,

01:47.797 --> 01:49.872
she'll be a smooth-faced wino.

01:50.041 --> 01:53.804
I'll add that to my list of 10,000 other
witch rules I'm supposed to follow.

01:53.969 --> 01:56.854
Would you mind terribly
if I asked for that in a crystal bowl?

01:57.015 --> 01:59.820
As an artist, I'm sensitive
about these things.

01:59.981 --> 02:02.022
Allow me.

02:02.466 --> 02:04.462
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

02:04.751 --> 02:06.826
ZELDA:
Sabrina, that was charitable.

02:06.995 --> 02:08.911
You didn't listen to a word I said.

02:09.080 --> 02:11.919
Oh, come on. Salem's not gonna
accomplish anything in his life.

02:12.086 --> 02:15.051
I'm still way ahead
of half the Kennedy children.

02:15.974 --> 02:18.892
Harvey, you're gonna be late
for Chemistry. What are you doing?

02:19.581 --> 02:21.257
Trying to open my locker.

02:21.424 --> 02:24.070
You think my gym shoes
could be causing a vacuum?

02:24.230 --> 02:26.466
SABRINA: <i>I know I'm not supposed
to do this, but I doubt</i>

02:26.635 --> 02:28.835
<i>there's a Nobel Prize
in Harvey's future.</i>

02:30.202 --> 02:32.038
Whoa, somebody's been working out.

02:32.206 --> 02:34.966
Sabrina, I've gotta ask you something.

02:35.132 --> 02:36.250
If it's about your hair,

02:36.415 --> 02:38.411
yes, it does look
like a woodland creature's home.

02:38.579 --> 02:39.936
Oh, yeah? Well, I

02:40.102 --> 02:42.302
didn't really have time
to fix it this morning.

02:42.467 --> 02:44.109
You know, Libby, speaking of hair,

02:44.270 --> 02:46.266
how's your chronic lice problem?

02:46.435 --> 02:48.795
I mean, you should be charging
those little fellows rent.

02:48.960 --> 02:50.795
That was great, Sabrina.

02:50.964 --> 02:54.042
Look, I hate to put you
in the position of having to say no,

02:54.210 --> 02:56.936
but my mom's always on me
about having a friend over for dinner,

02:57.096 --> 02:59.137
and I've been putting it
off for 13 years,

02:59.301 --> 03:00.703
but she's like a dog with a bone.

03:00.864 --> 03:02.780
Val, stop being so insecure.

03:02.948 --> 03:04.784
- I'd love to come over.
- Really?

03:04.952 --> 03:06.993
Tonight is charades night
at the Birkhead house.

03:07.156 --> 03:08.148
Sounds like fun,

03:08.319 --> 03:11.078
and it beats "throw out the
fuzzy food" night at my house.

03:11.245 --> 03:13.765
You know, painting has opened up
a whole new world for me.

03:13.930 --> 03:15.687
My soul is soaring.

03:15.854 --> 03:19.936
Now, how can I use
this God-given talent for material gain?

03:20.102 --> 03:23.546
I know. All I need is a human.

03:23.710 --> 03:25.193
Close enough.

03:25.353 --> 03:26.870
It smells like turpentine in here.

03:27.036 --> 03:28.759
Did you order from that
sushi place again?

03:28.920 --> 03:30.437
Do me a favour
and take these paintings

03:30.603 --> 03:32.564
down to that hip new gallery in town.

03:32.728 --> 03:34.644
You know, the one with all
the driftwood art.

03:34.812 --> 03:37.731
I can't. Brock's picking me up
for our date any minute.

03:37.898 --> 03:40.703
Besides, no gallery would ever
buy paintings done by a cat.

03:40.864 --> 03:42.347
How about if you're the painter?

03:42.507 --> 03:44.981
We'll split the commission
right down the middle: Eighty-20.

03:45.153 --> 03:46.145
[DOORBELL RINGS]

03:46.315 --> 03:48.356
But I don't like your paintings.
They're creepy.

03:48.519 --> 03:50.355
Why don't you paint
something pretty on velvet?

03:50.524 --> 03:52.724
Hilda, Brock's here.

03:52.888 --> 03:54.041
Who ordered sushi?

03:54.772 --> 03:56.688
- Hi, Hilda.
- Hi.

03:56.856 --> 03:58.452
Say, who's the artist in the family?

03:58.620 --> 04:00.023
These paintings are remarkable.

04:00.183 --> 04:02.908
Oh, it's really just a hobby.

04:03.670 --> 04:04.788
SALEM:
<i>Oh, yeah.</i>

04:07.397 --> 04:08.720
So you see, Sabrina,

04:08.880 --> 04:11.685
being a safety inspector
boils down to this:

04:11.846 --> 04:14.731
people pay me to do
their worrying for them.

04:14.892 --> 04:16.728
Do you get a bonus for panicking?

04:18.700 --> 04:21.459
By the way, Warren, I picked this up
for you on the way home.

04:21.625 --> 04:23.941
- Great bicycle helmet.
- Oh, no. We wear them in the car.

04:24.672 --> 04:27.317
Twenty bucks to keep
that information inside these walls.

04:27.478 --> 04:29.713
Have some chopped beets, Sabrina.

04:30.404 --> 04:31.442
Mom's a nutritionist.

04:31.606 --> 04:33.887
Everything we eat is healthy.

04:34.051 --> 04:36.126
I never said being my friend
would be easy.

04:36.295 --> 04:38.690
Don't worry. I can make
almost anything disappear.

04:39.903 --> 04:41.899
What a beautiful shade of red.

04:42.067 --> 04:45.431
I could use that colour
to create a masterpiece.

04:45.594 --> 04:47.715
No, I'll just eat it.

04:47.879 --> 04:52.040
Twenty-six, 27, 28.

04:52.728 --> 04:55.202
Now you may swallow.

04:55.374 --> 04:56.366
Hey, look, a wishbone.

04:56.536 --> 04:57.939
I once choked on a ham bone.

04:58.660 --> 05:00.462
Shut up. Shut up. Shut up.

05:00.624 --> 05:02.540
Why don't you and Mr. Birkhead
make a wish?

05:02.709 --> 05:05.354
No, thank you.
We're not the whimsical sort.

05:05.514 --> 05:06.837
Come on. Live a little.

05:06.997 --> 05:08.720
Well, all right, then.

05:08.881 --> 05:11.959
But everyone shield your eyes,
there may be bone shards.

05:12.127 --> 05:14.773
SABRINA: <i>I guess this is sort of
charity, but I'm so bored.</i>

05:14.933 --> 05:16.815
Make a good wish.

05:16.977 --> 05:18.654
<i>Their lives are so dry
Here's what we'll do</i>

05:18.821 --> 05:20.942
<i>Take whatever they wish
And make it come true</i>

05:22.108 --> 05:23.100
Ah.

05:24.272 --> 05:27.955
Okay, who wants, or is willing
to try, rhubarb pie?

05:28.120 --> 05:29.272
Yummy.

05:29.442 --> 05:30.845
[HUMMING]

05:31.366 --> 05:32.962
Looks like pie. I--

05:33.130 --> 05:34.532
[SNIFFING]

05:34.733 --> 05:36.375
Smells terrible.

05:36.537 --> 05:38.054
Bad colours. I don't--

05:38.220 --> 05:39.737
I won't eat this. I refuse to eat--

05:39.903 --> 05:41.181
[CHEWING]

05:41.587 --> 05:42.625
Strong.

05:42.789 --> 05:44.625
- Round.
- Round. Oh, I've got it.

05:44.793 --> 05:47.267
<i>The Effect of Gamma Rays
on Man-in-the-Moon Marigolds.</i>

05:47.438 --> 05:50.323
Wow.
I couldn't even get <i>Little Women.</i>

05:50.485 --> 05:51.887
I'm such a loser.

05:52.048 --> 05:54.089
Okay, that makes
the final charades score:

05:54.252 --> 05:57.171
Sabrina, 18.
Everyone else, two.

05:57.338 --> 05:58.695
Well, I really gotta get going.

05:58.861 --> 06:02.545
I'm really tired and no wonder.
It's 8:15.

06:02.709 --> 06:04.545
This is the latest
anyone has ever stayed,

06:04.713 --> 06:07.108
including blood relatives. Thank you.

06:07.278 --> 06:08.715
It was nice to see you, Sabrina.

06:08.882 --> 06:11.607
Dinner was terrific
and thanks for the recipe.

06:11.767 --> 06:14.686
That lima bean loaf
really did taste like tofu.

06:15.655 --> 06:17.571
Leave before she tries
to put some in a sack.

06:17.739 --> 06:18.858
Gotta go.

06:19.022 --> 06:21.018
You really livened up
our evening, Sabrina.

06:21.868 --> 06:24.833
In fact, that's what I wished for.

06:24.994 --> 06:28.756
That our Valerie would be happier
and more upbeat like you.

06:28.922 --> 06:32.970
SABRINA: <i>A happier Valerie.
What could be wrong with that?</i>

06:34.774 --> 06:36.609
So, what happened at the gallery?

06:36.778 --> 06:39.058
- They bought all the paintings.
- Yes.

06:39.222 --> 06:41.344
And they wanna have
an exhibition of your work.

06:41.507 --> 06:44.426
I mean, our work. I mean, my work.

06:44.593 --> 06:46.155
Don't you wanna hear
about my date?

06:46.317 --> 06:48.358
No. Let's see the money.

06:48.521 --> 06:50.562
Here.

06:51.888 --> 06:53.484
Why did you want it all in singles?

06:53.651 --> 06:54.929
SALEM:
So I can do this:

06:55.094 --> 06:58.378
I'm rich! Rich, I tell you!

06:58.541 --> 07:00.457
Salem, it's only
a few hundred dollars.

07:00.625 --> 07:03.385
I'm well-off! Well-off I tell you!

07:03.551 --> 07:04.954
[CHUCKLING]

07:07.279 --> 07:10.119
Hey, Sabrina,
that was really fun last night.

07:10.285 --> 07:13.922
For the first time in years I didn't have
my "naked in the Superdome" dream.

07:14.093 --> 07:15.370
I'm glad you're in a good mood.

07:15.535 --> 07:17.337
Yeah, I just feel different
for some reason.

07:17.499 --> 07:20.100
I'd like to thank the two of you
for always travelling together.

07:20.265 --> 07:22.705
It helps me insult you
that much more efficiently.

07:22.870 --> 07:24.866
Libby, better run along.
Aren't you late for your--

07:25.035 --> 07:27.794
"Future Bitter DivorcÃ©es
of America" meeting?

07:27.960 --> 07:31.005
My worst nightmare:
freaks in Sensurround.

07:32.249 --> 07:33.287
That felt great.

07:33.451 --> 07:36.256
Well, better get to Algebra II.

07:36.417 --> 07:39.177
She is more upbeat. Man, I'm good.

07:39.343 --> 07:42.627
"A 25-foot ladder is leaning
against a garage.

07:42.790 --> 07:45.310
Its base is 12 feet from the wall.

07:45.476 --> 07:47.277
How high up does the ladder reach?"

07:47.440 --> 07:48.671
Oh, I know. The ladder is--

07:48.842 --> 07:50.485
21.9 feet high.

07:50.646 --> 07:53.325
Why, Valerie,
that's another one right.

07:53.492 --> 07:57.049
Either you've been studying, or have
I been mouthing the answers again?

07:57.219 --> 07:59.135
No, Valerie's just becoming

07:59.303 --> 08:01.823
more like a person
that's good in math.

08:03.913 --> 08:07.230
So have you noticed
anything different about Valerie lately?

08:07.400 --> 08:08.552
Now that you mention it,

08:08.722 --> 08:12.120
she seems a lot more happy
and relaxed, like you.

08:12.289 --> 08:14.365
Oh, well, you mean that
she reminds you of me, right?

08:14.534 --> 08:17.134
Not that she's actually
becoming like me.

08:17.300 --> 08:20.617
Guys don't struggle
with issues like that.

08:21.708 --> 08:22.861
- Valerie, wait.
- I can't.

08:23.031 --> 08:24.788
I signed up to help
with Spanish tutoring.

08:24.955 --> 08:26.951
Me too.
Since when do you speak Spanish?

08:27.159 --> 08:28.197
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

08:28.362 --> 08:29.434
That's Spanish, you know.

08:29.604 --> 08:30.596
- Valerie--
- Sabrina--

08:30.767 --> 08:31.998
- You first.
- I just--

08:32.169 --> 08:33.572
- Stop!
- Stop!

08:33.732 --> 08:34.804
So weird.

08:34.975 --> 08:36.857
It's like we have
the same brain or something.

08:37.019 --> 08:38.855
Man, I'm late. Gotta go.

08:41.188 --> 08:42.784
- Oh, Sabrina.
- Hi, Mrs. Birkhead.

08:42.951 --> 08:46.474
- I was on my way to Science Club--
- Valerie said she's gonna join that.

08:46.639 --> 08:47.870
Oh, well, there's a surprise.

08:48.041 --> 08:49.364
Anyway, I was just wondering

08:49.524 --> 08:51.281
about the wish you made
the other night.

08:51.448 --> 08:53.090
Do you remember your exact words?

08:53.653 --> 08:57.370
I said, "I wish our Valerie
could be just like Sabrina."

08:57.540 --> 08:59.183
- "Just" like me?
- Uh-huh.

08:59.344 --> 09:00.940
Let me go get Valerie.

09:01.108 --> 09:02.100
Try and stay calm.

09:02.270 --> 09:04.835
It would be so unusual
for a spell to backfire on me.

09:04.995 --> 09:07.151
Hey, Sabrina.

09:08.202 --> 09:10.642
And they say
no one bats a thousand.

09:18.222 --> 09:21.141
Valerie, your hair
looks just like mine.

09:21.589 --> 09:23.550
I was gonna say
the same thing to you.

09:24.515 --> 09:26.157
Good morning, sweetheart.

09:26.799 --> 09:28.715
Hey, I could get used to that.

09:30.086 --> 09:33.051
Harvey, did you just do
what I think you did?

09:33.212 --> 09:35.287
You mean, kiss Valerie?

09:35.457 --> 09:36.940
But I kiss everyone.

09:37.100 --> 09:38.583
It's my Italian blood.

09:39.224 --> 09:40.296
[SPEAKS IN ITALIAN]

09:43.713 --> 09:45.355
You're Slovenian.

09:45.517 --> 09:48.117
Hey, I just got off
the phone with Brock.

09:48.282 --> 09:49.719
He asked me out on another date.

09:49.886 --> 09:52.280
I'll get in touch
with the people at Ripley's.

09:52.451 --> 09:54.127
I really think Brock might be the one.

09:54.294 --> 09:57.259
I mean, there's no posing,
there's no pretence.

09:57.421 --> 09:59.621
It's just a totally honest relationship.

09:59.785 --> 10:01.142
So you told him you're a witch?

10:01.309 --> 10:02.461
Of course not.

10:02.631 --> 10:04.513
Oh, by the way, the gallery called.

10:04.675 --> 10:06.797
They wanna pick up
some more of my paintings.

10:06.960 --> 10:08.032
Brock's so impressed.

10:08.202 --> 10:11.087
Fine, but I should inform you
that my style has evolved.

10:11.249 --> 10:12.446
I now work with found objects.

10:12.611 --> 10:15.895
Old bicycle inner tubes,
seashells, bio-waste,

10:16.058 --> 10:17.815
and incorporate them into my art.

10:17.982 --> 10:19.578
Sounds awful.

10:19.746 --> 10:21.742
I'm gonna be famous.

10:22.431 --> 10:28.280
Here we go. "Wishbone Spells.
See Sanders, Colonel. Page 387."

10:29.044 --> 10:31.929
What? Salem, there's paint
all over the page I need.

10:32.090 --> 10:35.295
- Do you have any idea why?
- I've been cleaning my brushes on it.

10:35.457 --> 10:38.980
I heard that Lichtenstein cleaned his
with Perrier and hundred dollar bills.

10:39.145 --> 10:40.137
Thanks a lot.

10:40.307 --> 10:42.907
I granted Mrs. Birkhead's wish
that Valerie be like me.

10:43.072 --> 10:45.353
Not just like you.

10:45.517 --> 10:47.878
Would we be having this conversation
if I had left it vague?

10:48.042 --> 10:50.243
This is bad.
Pretty soon there'll be two Sabrinas

10:50.407 --> 10:52.927
and Valerie will disappear forever.

10:53.093 --> 10:56.650
How can I phrase this in a way that will
capture the spirit of the moment?

10:56.820 --> 10:58.702
Help.

10:58.864 --> 10:59.902
Here's what you do:

11:00.067 --> 11:02.142
move to the Pacific Northwest
and live out your days

11:02.311 --> 11:03.383
under an assumed name.

11:03.554 --> 11:05.276
I recommend "Agnes."

11:05.437 --> 11:09.200
- Salem, you're useless.
- I'm an artist, not a logician.

11:09.365 --> 11:11.726
There's gotta be a way around this.

11:11.890 --> 11:13.088
Hey.

11:13.253 --> 11:15.773
If Valerie's acting like me,
all I have to do is start acting

11:15.938 --> 11:18.459
the way she used to act before
she started acting like me.

11:18.624 --> 11:21.464
She'll start acting like her old self
and stop acting like me. Get it?

11:21.630 --> 11:24.309
Would this be a bad time to tell you
you're sitting on paint?

11:28.283 --> 11:29.561
I have an idea.

11:29.726 --> 11:32.007
Have you ever thought
about dying your hair brown?

11:33.414 --> 11:35.136
Like it would make a difference.

11:35.297 --> 11:37.692
I just know I'm gonna flunk
next week's history test,

11:37.863 --> 11:39.459
the Science Club
wants to kick me out,

11:39.626 --> 11:41.987
and I'm pretty sure I'm the most
unpopular girl in school.

11:42.151 --> 11:44.272
- Really?
SABRINA: <i>Great, it's working.</i>

11:44.436 --> 11:48.198
Well, then I have to cheer you up
because life is great and you're great.

11:48.364 --> 11:50.165
<i>Jeez, am I really that obnoxious?</i>

11:50.328 --> 11:51.400
Come to dinner at my house.

11:51.570 --> 11:53.452
I know that my aunts
would love to see you.

11:53.614 --> 11:55.815
- Your aunts?
- Oops, I meant parents.

11:55.979 --> 11:57.176
I won't take no for an answer.

11:57.342 --> 11:58.619
See you tonight.

11:58.785 --> 12:01.943
I know this can work,
I just have to be twice as insecure.

12:02.111 --> 12:05.236
It's times like this I hate
coming from a loving environment.

12:05.879 --> 12:08.159
I just know I'm not
gonna get into college,

12:08.324 --> 12:10.559
and I'd bet anything Harvey's
gonna break up with me,

12:10.729 --> 12:14.126
and the economic instability in Russia
is really affecting my sleep.

12:14.777 --> 12:18.015
You will get into college,
Harvey won't break up with you,

12:18.184 --> 12:21.102
and Russia probably will collapse,
but we don't live there.

12:21.871 --> 12:24.995
Valerie has taught us so much
with her new upbeat attitude.

12:25.158 --> 12:27.962
It's like when I was looking over
these plans for a new bridge at work.

12:28.124 --> 12:31.841
I realised when I say, "not safe
for humans," I'm like a broken record.

12:32.011 --> 12:33.209
MRS. BIRKHEAD:
Everyone hungry?

12:33.374 --> 12:37.057
We've got fried chicken, onion rings,
fatback and crackling.

12:37.222 --> 12:39.138
Mom bought the new
Elvis recipe book.

12:39.306 --> 12:41.746
After dinner, can I go run
with scissors again?

12:41.911 --> 12:45.070
SABRINA: <i>This is gonna be
harder than I thought.</i>

12:45.238 --> 12:47.712
Salem, I've got bad news.

12:47.883 --> 12:51.486
I just got back from the gallery
and your latest paintings bombed.

12:51.651 --> 12:52.769
Oh, no.

12:52.933 --> 12:55.407
But the good news is
I've still got a date with Brock.

12:55.579 --> 12:57.814
He really likes the way
I handle setbacks.

12:57.984 --> 12:59.136
See you.

12:59.306 --> 13:01.587
Fame, you are a fickle mistress.

13:01.751 --> 13:04.146
Well, I still have my art,
and that's what's important.

13:04.316 --> 13:06.357
I got into this
because I love painting,

13:06.521 --> 13:08.961
not to get rich.

13:09.126 --> 13:10.278
[CRYING]

13:10.449 --> 13:11.521
Who am I kidding?

13:11.691 --> 13:14.896
I just made a down payment
on a mail-order bride.

13:15.058 --> 13:16.780
[CONTINUES CRYING]

13:18.264 --> 13:19.302
- Hi, Sabrina.
- Hey.

13:19.467 --> 13:20.505
Hey, Sabrina.

13:20.669 --> 13:23.474
You know, I'm thinking
of changing my name to Sabrina.

13:23.635 --> 13:25.596
I mean, after all,
it's what everyone calls me.

13:25.759 --> 13:27.436
"Sabrina Birkhead."

13:27.603 --> 13:29.803
No, no, no. "Sabrina Sirkhead."

13:29.968 --> 13:32.282
Sounds better with something
with an S, wouldn't you say?

13:32.453 --> 13:33.810
Is nothing sacred?

13:33.976 --> 13:35.777
Hey, Harvey,
what do you say you and I

13:35.940 --> 13:37.901
hit the Slicery this afternoon alone.

13:38.064 --> 13:39.182
I know I'll be hungry.

13:41.311 --> 13:43.831
Oh, that does it.

13:43.996 --> 13:46.391
Now it's time to play hardball.

13:46.561 --> 13:48.682
She's not stealing my life
or my boyfriend.

13:51.170 --> 13:53.771
Let's see if she still
wants to be like me.

13:56.221 --> 13:57.452
[GROWLS]

13:58.866 --> 14:01.706
Sabrina, has something
been bothering you?

14:01.872 --> 14:04.233
Anything with just
three chords ain't music.

14:04.397 --> 14:07.795
Believe me, Sabrina, I recognise
a cry for help when I see one.

14:07.964 --> 14:10.849
Perhaps you'd be more comfortable
speaking with someone your own age

14:11.010 --> 14:12.892
who's a little more mature.

14:13.054 --> 14:14.046
I know, Valerie.

14:17.062 --> 14:19.058
[SALEM SOBBING]

14:19.788 --> 14:22.467
Salem, you know, Vincent
van Gogh was a great artist,

14:22.634 --> 14:25.393
and he never sold a single
painting during his lifetime.

14:25.560 --> 14:26.552
SALEM:
Really?

14:26.722 --> 14:27.953
What a loser.

14:28.125 --> 14:29.243
[DOORBELL RINGS]

14:29.407 --> 14:30.445
Wonder who that is.

14:30.610 --> 14:33.050
Ooh, maybe it's Brock.

14:33.215 --> 14:36.659
- Who is it?
MAN: Delivery for Spellman.

14:40.469 --> 14:41.508
"Rest In Peace."

14:41.672 --> 14:43.588
"Deepest Sympathy."

14:43.756 --> 14:45.079
"Say hi to God for me"?

14:45.239 --> 14:47.600
Be glad you didn't get
our biggest seller: "Good Riddance."

14:49.047 --> 14:50.963
Hilda, did you know
you're in the newspaper?

14:51.131 --> 14:52.362
Really? Where?

14:52.534 --> 14:53.765
The obituary page.

14:53.937 --> 14:55.693
Have you died and not told me?

14:55.860 --> 14:58.985
Either the afterlife is a disappointment
of enormous proportions,

14:59.147 --> 15:01.826
or somebody owes me
an explanation. Salem?

15:01.993 --> 15:03.589
Look, everyone knows
a painter's paintings

15:03.756 --> 15:05.638
get more valuable after he dies.

15:05.800 --> 15:07.602
I'm just speeding up the process.

15:07.764 --> 15:11.766
I'm referred to
as your "long-time companion."

15:11.933 --> 15:14.328
Everyone is going to think
that I'm dead.

15:14.498 --> 15:15.935
SALEM:
What's the big deal?

15:16.101 --> 15:18.062
You don't leave the house
that much anyway.

15:19.949 --> 15:21.545
SABRINA:
<i>So this is how it ends.</i>

15:21.712 --> 15:24.837
<i>Me with a ring in my nose
and no way out of this mess.</i>

15:24.999 --> 15:27.564
<i>Well, at least the spell
can't get any worse.</i>

15:27.724 --> 15:31.692
Sabrina, you're not gonna believe this.
I have magical powers. Watch.

15:36.101 --> 15:38.701
The phrase "spiralling out
of control" comes to mind.

15:38.867 --> 15:40.863
Oh, don't worry.
I promise to use them responsibly.

15:41.031 --> 15:42.627
I'd never do anything
frivolous with them.

15:43.957 --> 15:46.431
What are you looking at, freaks?

15:46.602 --> 15:48.963
Well, most of the time.

15:50.210 --> 15:53.094
It looks like you don't quite have
a handle on that magic of yours.

15:53.256 --> 15:55.172
We better go somewhere
and figure out what to do.

15:55.340 --> 15:57.062
You're not gonna turn me
over to scientists,

15:57.224 --> 16:00.189
- or sell me to the government?
- Oh, of course not.

16:00.350 --> 16:02.072
Not right off the bat, anyway.

16:04.158 --> 16:07.795
I came over as soon
as I heard the news, Zelda.

16:07.965 --> 16:09.197
Tell me, how did it happen?

16:10.651 --> 16:12.053
Um...

16:12.775 --> 16:14.736
Would you excuse me
for a moment?

16:15.941 --> 16:18.016
Who do we invite to the wake?

16:18.186 --> 16:20.466
Hilda, Brock's here.

16:20.631 --> 16:22.193
Oh, that's right. We've got a date.

16:22.354 --> 16:24.635
Not so fast. He thinks you're dead.

16:24.799 --> 16:26.441
Well, when he sees me,
he'll know I'm not.

16:26.603 --> 16:27.595
SALEM:
You can't go in there.

16:27.765 --> 16:29.282
He's not as dumb as he looks.

16:29.448 --> 16:32.926
He'll know you faked your death
because your paintings weren't selling.

16:33.096 --> 16:36.653
- I'll tell him they weren't my paintings.
- And he'll know you've been untruthful.

16:36.823 --> 16:38.466
And the beautiful
relationship you two had

16:38.627 --> 16:42.470
will be tainted by lies and more lies.

16:42.635 --> 16:44.072
Just my luck.

16:44.238 --> 16:46.838
I meet the guy of my dreams,
but I die.

16:47.004 --> 16:49.204
I'll let him down gently.

16:49.368 --> 16:51.204
I know it's gotta hurt, Hilda,

16:51.372 --> 16:54.132
but you did kind
of bring it on yourself.

16:54.298 --> 16:55.336
Wait a minute.

16:55.501 --> 16:56.984
What am I talking to a cat for?

16:57.144 --> 16:59.026
I don't have to tell Brock
about the paintings.

16:59.188 --> 17:01.263
I'll tell him the newspaper
made a mistake.

17:01.433 --> 17:03.268
Hilda Spelminsky died.

17:03.437 --> 17:04.474
[CHUCKLING]

17:04.880 --> 17:06.476
Oh, there, there.

17:06.643 --> 17:08.479
It's okay to cry.

17:08.646 --> 17:12.045
Just use this tissue
instead of my blouse.

17:12.214 --> 17:15.098
Oh, sorry.

17:15.260 --> 17:16.333
Hi, Brock.

17:16.502 --> 17:18.305
The newspaper made a mistake.

17:19.108 --> 17:20.751
[SCREAMING]

17:23.637 --> 17:25.233
HILDA:
Brock.

17:25.401 --> 17:26.804
[BROCK SCREAMS]

17:28.165 --> 17:32.009
Okay, that's not the way
he usually greets me.

17:32.174 --> 17:35.174
Uh, sorry, but Brock said
he needed closure

17:35.341 --> 17:38.864
so I zapped in some photos
of you in a coffin.

17:39.549 --> 17:40.747
I'm so pale.

17:40.912 --> 17:42.429
You're dead.

17:42.595 --> 17:46.279
Okay, stay here and lay off the magic.
And I'll go figure out what to do.

17:46.443 --> 17:49.408
Look, I've been thinking about it
and it's gonna be so weird, Sabrina.

17:49.569 --> 17:50.926
I'm gonna have to hide my powers

17:51.092 --> 17:53.407
and make up all sorts of excuses
for the rest of my life.

17:53.577 --> 17:56.257
You have no idea what kind
of stress I'm gonna be under.

17:56.423 --> 17:58.704
Right. I have no idea.

18:00.191 --> 18:02.312
Have you guys got a minute?

18:02.475 --> 18:03.958
Oh, look, Hilda.

18:04.119 --> 18:06.240
Sabrina's going
through that charming

18:06.403 --> 18:10.451
"to assert my independence I'm making
myself as ugly as possible" phase.

18:10.612 --> 18:14.500
I'll explain later. I may have gotten in
a small problem with charitable magic.

18:14.660 --> 18:15.652
You did?

18:15.822 --> 18:18.821
Didn't you read the advisory by
the Witches' Council in my magazine?

18:18.989 --> 18:20.711
It couldn't have been more explicit.

18:20.872 --> 18:23.677
I blame the school system.
My retention's not what it should be.

18:24.520 --> 18:25.876
So now Valerie's a witch.

18:26.043 --> 18:27.605
Not a particularly good one, but still.

18:27.766 --> 18:28.884
All right, Sabrina.

18:29.490 --> 18:31.611
Here's what you have to do
to reverse the spell.

18:31.774 --> 18:33.531
First, change your clothes.

18:33.698 --> 18:35.819
There's no reason
to make the situation sadder.

18:38.147 --> 18:40.792
Ah. Then you've got to
take Valerie home

18:40.953 --> 18:43.108
and somehow convince
Mr. and Mrs. Birkhead

18:43.277 --> 18:45.923
to say, in these precise words:

18:46.083 --> 18:48.204
"We're happy Valerie changed."

18:48.368 --> 18:50.203
- Got it?
- Why do I want them to say that?

18:50.372 --> 18:53.097
I want them to be not happy
that Valerie has changed.

18:53.859 --> 18:55.342
We know it's ironic.

18:55.502 --> 18:56.779
We know it's illogical,

18:56.945 --> 18:58.017
but believe it or not,

18:58.187 --> 19:00.627
we know more about these things
than you do.

19:00.793 --> 19:01.831
Fine, okay.

19:01.995 --> 19:03.352
Shouldn't be very hard.

19:03.518 --> 19:06.163
Mr. and Mrs. Birkhead are
thrilled with the new Valerie.

19:07.366 --> 19:10.011
What happened?
You guys were so upbeat before.

19:10.171 --> 19:12.327
Remember that bridge
I was telling you about?

19:12.496 --> 19:15.574
It's still standing.
Twenty feet below sea level.

19:16.183 --> 19:21.748
I just got fired for recommending
a heart patient loosen up and try lard.

19:21.915 --> 19:24.480
Well, what about Warren?
I mean, you seem happy.

19:24.640 --> 19:26.317
[IN HOARSE VOICE]
I found out the hard way:

19:26.484 --> 19:28.207
electrical sockets are not toys.

19:28.368 --> 19:31.812
If you ask me, our troubles started
about the time Valerie changed.

19:31.975 --> 19:33.618
Oh, but you're glad
she changed, right?

19:33.779 --> 19:36.664
Not at all.
We miss the old Valerie.

19:36.825 --> 19:38.821
But you didn't realise how much
until she changed,

19:38.989 --> 19:40.871
so you're really glad she changed.

19:41.033 --> 19:43.234
- No.
- I see.

19:43.398 --> 19:45.040
Okay, I know what
will liven things up.

19:45.202 --> 19:46.559
Let's play charades.

19:46.725 --> 19:47.956
- Now?
- Now?

19:48.128 --> 19:49.120
I'll go first.

19:49.290 --> 19:53.816
It's not the name of a book or a movie.
It's just a particular phrase, okay?

19:53.979 --> 19:55.861
- Small?
- Tiny?

19:56.024 --> 19:59.866
- Wee?
- Yes. Okay, "we." Next word.

20:00.032 --> 20:01.947
Oh, I've got it. Happy.

20:02.116 --> 20:04.875
Okay, "We're happy--"

20:05.603 --> 20:08.407
- Valerie?
- Okay, "We're happy Valerie."

20:08.569 --> 20:10.724
- We're almost done.
- Mom, Dad,

20:10.893 --> 20:12.809
I can't keep it a secret any longer.

20:12.978 --> 20:15.019
I've got magical powers. Watch.

20:18.108 --> 20:20.628
Valerie, you changed
Warren into a dingo.

20:20.793 --> 20:21.991
"Changed." You said "changed."

20:22.156 --> 20:24.882
You said,
"We're happy Valerie changed."

20:28.729 --> 20:31.694
Uh, did I just see
what I thought I saw?

20:31.856 --> 20:33.737
Of course not.
It's that crackpot diet of yours.

20:33.900 --> 20:36.340
You eat enough pastrami
and bear claws,

20:36.505 --> 20:38.022
you're gonna start seeing things.

20:38.188 --> 20:40.424
What--? What happened?
How did I get here?

20:40.593 --> 20:43.067
You seemed to believe
you had magical powers, dear.

20:43.238 --> 20:46.876
You tried to change Warren
into a dingo.

20:47.046 --> 20:49.327
I did? I am such a loser.

20:49.491 --> 20:50.643
[CRYING]

20:50.814 --> 20:53.858
Oh, our baby, she's back.

20:58.750 --> 21:00.267
SABRINA: That's all?
- Yes.

21:00.433 --> 21:02.394
You've gotta read
and chronologically organise

21:02.557 --> 21:05.122
all of your aunt Zelda's
<i>Enchanted By</i> magazines.

21:05.283 --> 21:06.845
Then we'll consider the matter settled.

21:07.006 --> 21:09.047
And to make sure you actually
read and don't skim,

21:09.211 --> 21:11.366
there will be a quiz
when you're done.

21:11.535 --> 21:12.527
Fine by me.

21:12.698 --> 21:14.294
As a frequent victim
of your punishments,

21:14.461 --> 21:16.023
I'd say you guys are getting soft.

21:17.026 --> 21:18.018
SABRINA:
Whoa.

21:18.189 --> 21:21.073
Did I mention that I've been
a loyal <i>Enchanted By</i> subscriber

21:21.235 --> 21:23.549
for over 375 years?

21:23.720 --> 21:25.076
Believe it or not, this is nothing

21:25.243 --> 21:26.839
compared to the <i>International Male</i>

21:27.006 --> 21:28.568
she's got stacked in the basement.

21:28.730 --> 21:29.848
This is child abuse.

21:30.012 --> 21:31.735
Do you know how many
paper cuts I could get?

21:31.896 --> 21:33.812
SALEM:
You think you've got it bad?

21:34.541 --> 21:36.697
And I'm supposed
to be on my honeymoon.

21:36.866 --> 21:38.383
[CRYING]

